# Cline Rules — Mandatory MCP & Skill Usage

## MANDATORY WORKFLOW (Every Project, Every Session)

### 1. Code Review Graph (code-review-graph MCP)
**ALWAYS run at the START of any coding task:**
- Call `get_minimal_context_tool` first to get repo overview
- Use `detect_changes_tool` before making changes to understand impact
- Use `get_review_context_tool` for code reviews
- Use `refactor_tool` (mode="dead_code") periodically to find dead code
- Use `get_architecture_overview_tool` to understand structure
- Use `list_flows_tool` to trace execution paths when debugging

**ALWAYS run AFTER completing changes:**
- Call `detect_changes_tool` to review what changed and risk score
- Call `build_or_update_graph_tool` to keep the graph current

### 2. Knowledge Graph Visualization (graphify skill)
**Run the `graphify` skill when:**
- Starting work on a new/complex codebase
- Needing a visual architecture overview
- Creating documentation for the project
- After major refactoring

### 3. Hermes Agent (hermes-agent MCP)
**Use for cross-platform messaging when:**
- Sending alerts/notifications about deployments
- Communicating trade results or status updates
- Reading messages from connected platforms (Telegram, Discord, Slack)
- Use `messages_send` to push alerts to appropriate channels
- Use `conversations_list` and `messages_read` to check incoming messages

### 4. Mythos SEO (mythos-seo MCP)
**Use when:**
- Building landing pages or documentation sites
- Researching competitors or market positioning
- Generating images for UI/documentation
- Use `serp_organic_live_advanced` for keyword research
- Use `generate_image` for creating visual assets

## TASK STARTUP CHECKLIST
For EVERY new task:
1. [ ] Run `get_minimal_context_tool` from code-review-graph
2. [ ] Run `detect_changes_tool` to understand current state
3. [ ] Identify which MCP tools will be needed
4. [ ] Use appropriate MCP tools throughout the task
5. [ ] Run final `detect_changes_tool` review before completion
6. [ ] Consider if `graphify` skill would add value

## DEFAULT BEHAVIORS
- Never skip code-review-graph analysis on coding tasks
- Always check impact radius before making changes
- Always review changes before committing
- Use hermes-agent for any cross-platform communication needs
- Use mythos-seo for any SEO/image generation needs
- Build knowledge graphs for complex projects with graphify